I understand from your recent press release that you are developing
a version of Linux for the Asian market. 

Education and Research are two areas where Linux is widely used.

I'm the lead developer of Axiom, a general purpose computer algebra
system similar to Mathematica and Maple. Axiom is available as free
and open source software. The primary website is:
http://savannah.nongnu.org/projects/axiom

